##
## Airlock Digital Add-on for Splunk v1.1.0
##

== About ==
This TA for Airlock Digital provides the data parsing required to process Airlock Digital syslog events.

This Add-on will perform the following actions by default:
1) Create an index called 'Airlock';
2) Open UDP:5514 to recieve Airlock syslog data.

If you wish to modify the port data is recieved on, please update the configuration in 'inputs.conf'.
If you wish to place Airlock data in another index please delete 'indexes.conf' and update the configuration in 'inputs.conf'.

== Installation ==
1) Please install the TA_airlock by extracting the files into the Splunk Apps subdirectory OR install through the Splunk UI;
2) After data is being recieved, please install the Airlock Digital App for Splunk https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3346/ for Dashboards.

== Troubleshooting ==
Please ensure the index that data is being written to can be searched by users.

